25 Section 14 prohibits persons from taking certain actions that restrict the ability of an
26 agricultural worker to enter or leave the residence of the agricultural worker.
27 Additionally, section 15, with certain exceptions, prohibits certain conduct related to
28 weeding or thinning by hand or using a short-handed hoe in a stooped, kneeling or squatting
29 position.
30 Section 16 requires agricultural employers to post certain notices related to the provisions
31 established in sections 11-15.
32 Section 17 requires agricultural employers, during periods of emergency or disaster, to:
33 (1) meet certain requirements related to housing provided to agricultural workers; and (2)
34 supply certain information to the agricultural workers.
35 Section 19 authorizes agricultural workers to organize and form collective bargaining
36 units.
37 Section 20 establishes a civil remedy for certain persons who are aggrieved by violations
38 of the Agricultural Workers’ Bill of Rights.
